Manchester City Beats Tottenham 5-1 to Maintain Winning Start to Season

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-08-28T14:24:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/man-city-beats-tottenham-5-1-maintains-winning-start-in-premier-league.html
Edin Dzeko got four goals as
Manchester City beat Tottenham 5-1 to maintain its winning start
to the season in English soccer’s Premier League.  Sergio Aguero  also scored at Tottenham’s White Hart Lane
stadium, with Younes Kaboul replying for the home team.  Earlier, Newcastle beat Fulham 2-1. Manchester United hosts
Arsenal, while West Bromwich Albion plays Stoke City.  Yesterday, Chelsea defeated Norwich 3-1, Liverpool beat
Bolton 3-1, Wigan won 2-0 against Queens Park Rangers, and
Everton won 1-0 at Blackburn. There were no goals in the matches
between  Aston Villa  and Wolverhampton Wanderers, and Swansea and
Sunderland.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  